to Evangelical Christianity.

00:13:48.120 --> 00:13:51.110
And in that one moment, all of the interest
disappeared.

00:13:51.110 --> 00:13:52.200
[laughter]

00:13:52.200 --> 00:13:56.600
And then we all had to laugh, even though
we're try and keep quiet until the end of

00:13:56.600 --> 00:13:57.600
the task.

00:13:57.600 --> 00:14:01.230
And they're like, "What?

00:14:01.230 --> 00:14:02.230
What's going on?"

00:14:02.230 --> 00:14:03.230
So, we explained it.

00:14:03.230 --> 00:14:06.720
And she said, "Oh, that's actually not me
or even my immediate family."

00:14:06.720 --> 00:14:08.540
Because what she meant, she was from Latin
America.

00:14:08.540 --> 00:14:13.880
So when she said her family, she meant like
her 30 closest relatives.

00:14:13.880 --> 00:14:15.519
And even not her immediate family.

00:14:15.519 --> 00:14:18.480
So the definition of family was different.

00:14:18.480 --> 00:14:23.259
And so then you would think after explaining
that this was something that OK, maybe he

00:14:23.259 --> 00:14:24.660
might be more open.

00:14:24.660 --> 00:14:25.680
He wasn't.

00:14:25.680 --> 00:14:28.790
