00:29:28.160 --> 00:29:29.620
and weighing those all at once.

00:29:29.620 --> 00:29:33.790
You see this is very active for economics
graduate students.

00:29:33.790 --> 00:29:34.960
And then there's not just me.

00:29:34.960 --> 00:29:36.560
Like, this is known in the literature.

00:29:36.560 --> 00:29:39.920
This is very active for econ graduate students.

00:29:39.920 --> 00:29:44.060
And so, right there, we can just see by these
red regions here that I've given you some

00:29:44.060 --> 00:29:48.200
idea of the analytical skills of ESTP.

00:29:48.200 --> 00:29:50.470
Maybe they don't show them all the time.

00:29:50.470 --> 00:29:52.900
Notice that none of these here are connected
to--.

00:29:52.900 --> 00:29:59.650
Well, I suppose there's a little bit of adjacency
over here and a little bit here on the corners,

00:29:59.650 --> 00:30:02.840
but they're not immediately adjacent to the
speaking areas.

00:30:02.840 --> 00:30:05.630
So they may not necessarily verbalize what
they're saying.

00:30:05.630 --> 00:30:08.370
It goes on in the interior of the neocortex.

00:30:08.370 --> 00:30:14.120
I think this is the part where I normally
ask if there are any questions.

00:30:14.120 --> 00:30:17.910
I don't think I've lost anyone.

00:30:17.910 --> 00:30:18.910
OK.

00:30:18.910 --> 00:30:21.590
I also know I'm supposed to count to five
