almost identical brain activity to them?

01:06:51.950 --> 01:06:53.920
It's that little slice up there.

01:06:53.920 --> 01:06:54.920
That's your percent chance.

01:06:54.920 --> 01:06:56.660
It's like three percent.

01:06:56.660 --> 01:07:02.200
However, there's a huge percentage chance,
50 percent, something over 50 percent that

01:07:02.200 --> 01:07:04.580
you'll have mostly the same activity.

01:07:04.580 --> 01:07:06.130
It turns out to be like 80 percent.

01:07:06.130 --> 01:07:08.820
You'll have 80 percent of your brain activity
in common.

01:07:08.820 --> 01:07:14.960
You also have a big chunk, say 35 percent
chance, that you will have half of your brain

01:07:14.960 --> 01:07:17.260
activity in common.

01:07:17.260 --> 01:07:20.940
And then, this sliver here, up here with the
purple, which I forget what percentage that

01:07:20.940 --> 01:07:21.940
is.

01:07:21.940 --> 01:07:25.300
You all can add up and find the difference
off of a hundred percent.

01:07:25.300 --> 01:07:27.880
And that's a chance you only have somewhat
similar.

01:07:27.880 --> 01:07:31.940
So, by the way, that's much better than if
we just compare any two people randomly in

01:07:31.940 --> 01:07:32.940
the population.

01:07:32.940 --> 01:07:38.250
So, like EFPN, ESTP, the chance that you'll
have almost identical or mostly similar brain

01:07:38.250 --> 01:07:39.360
activity is like almost nothing.

01:07:39.360 --> 01:07:40.650
It's very small.

01:07:40.650 --> 01:07:45.570
So, really good validation in terms of does
type actually point personality type point

01:07:45.570 --> 01:07:47.690
to something, it does.

01:07:47.690 --> 01:07:53.450
But it is not an assurance because you can
have two ENFPs say, and they might have quite

01:07:53.450 --> 01:07:54.750
different brain activity.

01:07:54.750 --> 01:07:59.090
Now, you'll still show the Christmas tree,
